bibdata.title: Status label is nil in certain situations

comments.body:
The response I get from https://bibdata.princeton.edu/bibliographic/99125378834306421/holdings/22897184810006421/availability.json? is:
[
{
"barcode": "",
"id": "23897184800006421",
"holding_id": "22897184810006421",
"copy_number": "1",
"status": "Not Available",
"status_label": "Acquisition",
"status_source": "process_type",
"process_type": "ACQ",
"on_reserve": "N",
"item_type": "Gen",
"pickup_location_id": "recap",
"pickup_location_code": "recap",
"location": "recap$pa",
"label": "ReCAP - Remote Storage",
"description": "",
"enum_display": "",
"chron_display": "",
"in_temp_library": false
}
]

@carolyncole where did you get the nil status response from?
The item must have been updated in Alma since the status is not nil anymore.

I would suggest that we update bib data to log the `mms_id` if we get nil from Alma on that specific field. That way we will have more information if/when the issue happens again. Perhaps log it as a WARN.

@carolyncole checked through the response again and it was not a bibdata issue it is a requests issue. I don't think also there is a possibility in alma to have an item in a process type and missing information on the label that we get from there.

> I would suggest that we update bib data to log the `mms_id` if we get nil from Alma on that specific field. That way we will have more information if/when the issue happens again. Perhaps log it as a WARN.

@hectorcorrea if you would like open a new issue for your suggestion?

figgy.title: "Attach an existing resource by ID" on record page does not remove the attached resource from its previous parent.

comments.body:
When reindexing at 500/batch Solr8 threw a timeout error. Trying to run it with 100/batch and pointed directly at the leader now. I also disabled soft commits by overriding `Valkyrie::Persistence::Solr::Repository::COMMIT_PARAMS = {}.freeze` before the task ran.

Current estimate is 14 hours for 6,724,594 objects, but it just started so that estimate will probably go up.

Error below:
```
**2021-09-16 23:34:00.233 ERROR (qtp2081191879-918) [c:figgy-production s:shard1 r:core_node6 x:figgy-production_shard1_replica_n4] o.a.s.u.SolrCmdDistributor java.io.IOException: Request processing has stalled for 20095ms with 100 remaining elements in the queue.
        at org.apache.solr.client.solrj.impl.ConcurrentUpdateHttp2SolrClient.request(ConcurrentUpdateHttp2SolrClient.java:448)
        at org.apache.solr.client.solrj.SolrClient.request(SolrClient.java:1290)
        at org.apache.solr.update.SolrCmdDistributor.doRequest(SolrCmdDistributor.java:344)
        at org.apache.solr.update.SolrCmdDistributor.submit(SolrCmdDistributor.java:337)**
```
